Correct - chalk is cheap, so are chalk boards. This solution would eliminate the need for chalk and chalk boards. The upfront costs would be more (obviously) than chalk/chalkboards - but a writing instrument like these would not need to be replaced (until it literally breaks). Also - the base doesn't have to be expensive, it can be wood with the pressure sensitive coating on top.
At it's core, this is an upfront investment - similar to solar panels - that pays for itself in the long run.
@Vincent, VERY similar to that.
